<Base title="Terms & Conditions · Padel Community India" description="Membership terms for Padel Community India (PCI). Read before applying.">

<header class="terms-header">
  <a href="/" class="header-brand">Padel Community India</a>
  <a href="/pune/casa-de-padel/evening" class="header-back">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="15 18 9 12 15 6"/></svg>
    Back to brochure
  </a>
</header>

<div class="hero-terms">
  <div class="hero-eyebrow">Padel Community India (PCI) · Casa De Padel, Kharadi</div>
  <h1 class="hero-title">Terms &amp;<br>Conditions</h1>
  <p class="hero-sub">These terms govern your membership in the PCI community. Please read them carefully before applying. By joining and making payment, you agree to everything below.</p>
</div>

<div class="terms-body">

  <div class="term-block">
    <div class="term-number">01</div>
    <div class="term-title">Membership &amp; Payment</div>
    <div class="term-body">Membership fees are due upfront before the start of each billing period. Access to the community, courts, and all included benefits begins only upon confirmed payment. <strong>Fees are non-refundable once a period has begun.</strong> No exceptions for partial months, missed sessions, travel, injury, or personal circumstances. Membership may be transferred to another player, subject to that player meeting the community's skill level requirements and receiving PCI approval.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="term-block">
    <div class="term-number">02</div>
    <div class="term-title">Spot Reservation</div>
    <div class="term-body">Monthly members hold their spot for the current month only. Members on quarterly, 6-month, or annual plans have their spot secured for the full duration of their plan. <strong>If a monthly member does not renew before the end of their current month, their spot may be offered to a waitlisted member</strong> or someone who has paid in advance for the following period. No notice will be required before reassigning an unreserved spot.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="term-block">
    <div class="term-number">03</div>
    <div class="term-title">Daily Registration &amp; Cancellations</div>
    <div class="term-body">Members must register on Reclub for each session they intend to attend. If you cannot make it, <strong>you must cancel at least 6 hours before the session begins.</strong> More than 2 cancellations in a calendar month, whether late or unannounced, may result in a formal warning or termination of membership at PCI's discretion. Consistent non-attendance without notice is considered a breach of community conduct.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="term-block">
    <div class="term-number">04</div>
    <div class="term-title">Code of Conduct</div>
    <div class="term-body">Members are expected to maintain sportsmanship, respect, and fair play at all times on court and in the community group. <strong>Behaviour that disrupts the experience for other members will not be tolerated.</strong> This includes but is not limited to: aggression or hostility, consistent late arrival without notice, disrespecting the venue or staff, and conduct unbecoming of the community's spirit.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="term-block">
    <div class="term-number">05</div>
    <div class="term-title">Removal &amp; Bans</div>
    <div class="term-body">PCI reserves the right to remove any member from the community at any time, for any reason that affects the integrity, safety, or experience of the group. <strong>In the event of removal for misconduct or rule violations, a pro-rata refund will be issued for the unused remaining days</strong> of the current paid period, calculated from the date of removal. No refund will be issued for days already elapsed. PCI's decision is final.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="term-block">
    <div class="term-number">06</div>
    <div class="term-title">Voluntary Exit</div>
    <div class="term-body">Members who choose to leave the community voluntarily mid-period are <strong>not entitled to a refund for any remaining days.</strong> If you are on a quarterly, 6-month, or annual plan and wish to exit early, your spot will be released to the waitlist and no partial refund will be provided.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="term-block">
    <div class="term-number">07</div>
    <div class="term-title">Guests</div>
    <div class="term-body">Members may bring a guest only when player numbers are short for that session, or when all players attending that night are in agreement. <strong>PCI has final say on whether a guest may participate.</strong> Guests must adhere to the same standards of conduct as members. Repeated issues with guests brought by a member may affect that member's standing in the community.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="term-block">
    <div class="term-number">08</div>
    <div class="term-title">Changes to the Community</div>
    <div class="term-body">PCI reserves the right to adjust session timings, court allocations, community rules, and pricing for future periods with reasonable prior notice. <strong>Changes will not affect a member's current paid period.</strong> Members will be informed of any material changes before their next renewal date.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="term-block">
    <div class="term-number">09</div>
    <div class="term-title">Transfers &amp; Network Growth</div>
    <div class="term-body">As the PCI network grows across other time slots and venues, members may be offered the option to transfer to another group. Membership may also be transferred to another player <strong>provided the incoming player meets the community's skill level requirements and is approved by PCI.</strong> Transfers are not guaranteed and are subject to spot availability. No refund entitlement arises from a transfer request that cannot be accommodated.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="term-block">
    <div class="term-number">10</div>
    <div class="term-title">Coaching Add-on</div>
    <div class="term-body">The coaching add-on is a separate optional subscription of ₹5,000/month billed alongside your base plan. It includes 20 minutes of 1-on-1 coaching per week and 2 hours of group drills every weekend. <strong>The coaching add-on is non-refundable once a month has begun.</strong> Missed 1-on-1 slots cannot be carried over. The add-on can be cancelled at the end of any billing month with notice before renewal.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="term-block">
    <div class="term-number">11</div>
    <div class="term-title">Liability</div>
    <div class="term-body">Participation in padel involves physical activity and an inherent risk of injury. <strong>Members participate entirely at their own risk.</strong> PCI, its operators, and partner venues are not liable for any injury, loss, or damage whether to person or property arising from participation in sessions. Members are advised to confirm they are in good physical health and medically fit to play before joining.</div>
  </div>

</div>

<div class="acceptance">
  <p><strong>By joining Padel Community India and making payment, you confirm that you have read, understood, and agree to all of the above terms.</strong> These terms are effective as of 1st July 2026 and may be updated from time to time. Members will be notified of any material changes before their next renewal.</p>
</div>

